         <c level="series">
            <did><unittitle>Series II: Writings and Notes, Undated, <unitdate type="inclusive">1986-1996</unitdate>
                    </unittitle>
            </did>
                <scopecontent><p>The Writings and Notes Series includes research notes and manuscript drafts of many of Poirier's scholarly articles, books, and book reviews as well as some copies of published articles.  These files are arranged topically by the subject of a work according to Poirier's own organizational and naming schemes.  Therefore, researchers seeking material related to the book <title render="italic">The Renewal of Literature,</title> should look under "Emerson, Ralph Waldo" rather than the title of the book.</p>
               <p>This series also includes some lecture notes and teaching material, including student essays from a 1986 course Poirier taught at Rutgers.  These student papers are restricted until 2056.</p>
                </scopecontent>
